            . I am in the service of Messrs. Barbers. On the 5th of January I went to Mr. Lewis's shop, and told the prisoner I came to pay Mr. Baker's account, which was 1 l. 16 s. 6 d., I cannot say exactly how I paid him, but am sure I gave him a sovereign and silver, or two sovereigns and received change - I produce the bill, with the receipt to it, which he gave me.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 23.</p>
